duck: Veterans of Future Wars - Veterans of Future Wars (VFW) was an organization formed as a prank by Princeton University students in 1936.
Veterans of Foreign Wars - The Veterans of Foreign Wars of the United States is a congressionally chartered war veterans organization in the United States.
VFW Parkway - VFW Parkway is a historic parkway in Boston, Massachusetts.
vfw definition: Veterans of Foreign Wars.
Vereinigte Flugtechnische Werke - Vereinigte Flugtechnische Werke (VFW) was a German aerospace company formed by the 1964 merger of Focke-Wulf and Weser Flugzeugbau GmbH (Weserflug).
Video for Windows - Video for Windows, also referred to as Video Compression Manager, was a multimedia framework developed by Microsoft that allowed Microsoft Windows to play digital video.

The 'Veterans of Foreign Wars of the United States (VFW)' is a congressionally
chartered [http://uscode.house.gov/download/pls/36C2301.txt (Title 36 USC
Chapter 2301)] war veterans organization in the United States. Headquartered in
Kansas City, Missouri, VFW currently has 1.5 million members belonging to 7,644
posts, and is the largest American organization of combat veterans.
